@startuml Sequence_Exam_Generation
' ──────────────────────────────────────────
'  Compile: https://www.plantuml.com/plantuml/uml
'  Paste this code → click Submit → download PNG
' ──────────────────────────────────────────

skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #6C47B8
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #EDE7F6
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #6C47B8
skinparam sequenceDividerBackgroundColor #F5F2F7
skinparam noteBorderColor #E8722A
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFF3E0

actor "Élève" as Eleve
participant "React\nMockExamsPage" as UI
participant "FastAPI\nPOST /api/generate-exam" as API
participant "FileCache" as FC
participant "GeminiService" as GS
participant "pdflatex" as TEX
database "GridFS" as GFS

Eleve -> UI : Sélectionne chapitres\n+ clique "Générer"
UI -> API : POST /api/generate-exam\n(subject, level, specialty,\nchapters, language,\ncourse_pdf_id, exam_pdf_id)

== 1. Chargement des PDF de référence ==
API -> FC : get_or_upload(course_pdf_id)
FC --> API : course_uri
API -> FC : get_or_upload(exam_pdf_id)
FC --> API : exam_uri

== 2. Génération LaTeX ==
API -> GS : generate_raw(exam_prompt,\n[course_pdf, exam_pdf, instructions])
note right : Prompt spécialisé :\nformat examen marocain,\nbarème, types de questions
GS --> API : code LaTeX complet\n(\\documentclass ... \\end{document})

== 3. Nettoyage du code ==
API -> API : Suppression code fences\nExtraction depuis \\documentclass

== 4. Compilation LaTeX ==
API -> TEX : pdflatex -interaction=nonstopmode\n(passe 1/2)
TEX --> API : exam.pdf
API -> TEX : pdflatex (passe 2/2)
TEX --> API : exam.pdf (final)

== 5. Stockage ==
API -> GFS : store_pdf(exam_bytes,\nmetadata={type: "exams", ...})
GFS --> API : file_id

API --> UI : {file_id, latex_code}
UI --> Eleve : PDF affiché dans le visualiseur

@enduml
